          "text": "Perfect! I've completed the fault localization analysis. Here's a summary of my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Summary\n\n**Buggy File**: `drivers/acpi/video_detect.c`\n\n**Buggy Components**:\n1. **Data Structure**: `video_detect_dmi_table[]` - The DMI quirks lookup table\n2. **Related Function**: `acpi_video_get_backlight_type()` - Backlight type selection logic\n\n**Root Cause**:\nThe Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the `video_detect_dmi_table[]`. Without this entry, the system incorrectly defaults to using ACPI video backlight (which doesn't work on this laptop) instead of native backlight (which does work).\n\n**Evidence**:\n- \u2705 Bug report confirms `acpi_backlight=native` fixes the issue\n- \u2705 Code shows cmdline parameters override DMI and default detection\n- \u2705 Without a DMI entry, the system falls back to `acpi_backlight_video` (line 449)\n- \u2705 Similar entries for other laptops already exist in the table (lines 287-354)\n\n**Confidence**: 0.95 (Very High)\n\nThe fault localization result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json` with detailed reasoning.",
